==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetrakosane
<hw>Tet"ra*ko*sane`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetra-</ets> + Gr. <?/ twenty.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A hydrocarbon, <chform>C24H50</chform>, resembling paraffin, and
like it belonging to the marsh-gas series; -- so called from having
<xex>twenty-four</xex> atoms of carbon in the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

